# Quartz Geode - Requirements

## Overview
This requirement specification details the design, functionality, and behavior of the Quartz geode within the game "Petrified," a turn-based strategy board game. Quartz is one of the five base geodes in the faction known as "The Crystalline Guard," as defined in @faction.req. It is visually distinct as a white or clear piece, providing a versatile movement ability that allows it to traverse any number of spaces in any direction on the 5x5 grid board, subject to fissure rules from @fissure-cell.req (e.g., entry blocked or permitted based on fissure orientations). Additionally, Quartz possesses a special fissure manipulation power, enabling it to turn or flip fissure cells as part of its strategic capabilities, integrating with board mechanics to alter movement paths for all geodes. This geode promotes flexible positioning and control over the board's dynamic elements, contributing to the game's objective of eroding the opponent's Pyrite geode. Operationally, Quartz supports turn-based gameplay in a web-based environment, with real-time validation ensuring balanced engagement.

## Functional Requirements
- FR-1: Quartz shall be implemented as a visually distinct game piece colored white or clear, as specified in ui-ux.req.md, with optional glow effects for activation to enhance usability.
- FR-2: Quartz shall have the ability to move any number of spaces in any direction (horizontal, vertical, or diagonal) on the 5x5 grid, provided the path adheres to fissure rules (e.g., blocked from entering cells with incompatible orientations, such as "+" symbol blocking diagonal entry or "X" symbol blocking horizontal/vertical entry, per @fissure-cell.req FR-13 and FR-14).
- FR-3: Quartz shall be capable of entering or traversing fissure cells based on their current orientation, with no inherent restrictions beyond standard fissure mechanics (e.g., allowed in default "+" orientation for horizontal/vertical movement and rotated "X" orientation for diagonal movement).
- FR-4: Quartz shall possess a special fissure manipulation power, allowing the controlling player to turn a standard fissure cell by 45-degree increments or flip the center fissure as a valid action during their turn, subject to the rules in @fissure-cell.req (e.g., cannot manipulate the same standard fissure in consecutive turns, but can flip the center fissure sequentially with opponents).
- FR-5: The fissure manipulation action for Quartz shall consume the player's turn, preventing simultaneous movement of Quartz in the same turn, and must be validated in real-time by the rules engine to ensure compliance (e.g., no manipulation during opponent's turn or after another action).
- FR-6: Quartz shall follow standard capture mechanics: it can capture opponent geodes by landing on their occupied cell, removing the opponent's piece from the board, unless overridden by specific geode powers (e.g., no special enhancements like Rose Quartz's).
